  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best free and legal music download sites?",
  "response": "There are several reputable websites where you can download music legally and for free. Here's a list of some of the best options:\n\n1. **SoundCloud**:\n   - SoundCloud is a popular platform for artists to share their music. Many artists offer free downloads of their tracks.\n   - **How to Use**: Look for the \"Download\" button on tracks. Some tracks might require you to follow the artist or log in to download.\n\n2. **Jamendo**:\n   - Jamendo offers a vast library of independent music, all of which is available for free under Creative Commons licenses.\n   - **How to Use**: Simply search for music, and you can download albums or individual tracks directly from the site.\n\n3. **Free Music Archive (FMA)**:\n   - The Free Music Archive is curated by WFMU, and it offers a wide range of genres, all available for free download.\n   - **How to Use**: Browse or search for music, and click the download button next to the track you want.\n\n4. **Bandcamp**:\n   - Bandcamp is known for allowing artists to sell their music directly to fans, but many artists also offer free downloads.\n   - **How to Use**: Look for the \"Buy Now\" or \"Free Download\" buttons on artist pages. Some artists might ask for an email address or a social media follow in exchange for the download.\n\n5. **NoiseTrade**:\n   - NoiseTrade specializes in free music from indie artists. In exchange for a download, you typically provide your email address.\n   - **How to Use**: Browse the music, select what you want, and enter your email address to receive a download link.\n\n6. **Last.fm**:\n   - Last.fm offers free music downloads in its \"Free Music Downloads\" section, although availability can vary.\n   - **How to Use**: Navigate to the \"Free Music Downloads\" section and download available tracks.\n\n7. **ccMixter**:\n   - ccMixter is a community music site featuring remixes and original music under Creative Commons licenses.\n   - **How to Use**: Browse or search for music, and download tracks directly from the site.\n\n8. **Musopen**:\n   - Musopen provides free classical music downloads, including recordings and sheet music.\n   - **How to Use**: Browse the collections and download the music files you want.\n\nWhen downloading music from these sites, always ensure you're respecting the terms of use and any Creative Commons licenses that may apply. Enjoy your free, legal music!",
